"Alone we gain hope, together we gain victory."

Millennia of wandering brought the humans into contact with every other race living in the world of TERA. Their knowledge and understanding of the civilized races made them the perfect coordinators for building an allied society. The Valkyon Federation represents a new hope for the world, with humans at its core.
"Cunning, fiery, and ready to seize their destiny."

Known for their dark, wry humor and bold manner, castanics refuse to be chained to their dark past, and strive each day to forge a new future. Fierce and independent, castanics make superb allies...or deadly enemies.
"Freedom and honor are not given, but earned."

Given their history as warrior-slaves to the giants, amani are enthusiastic about the new era of equality represented by the Valkyon Federation. The amani strive to suppress the violent nature forced upon them by their ancient overlords, but given provocation it rises to the surface.

Nature guardians awakened by the elins, the poporis live harmoniously in the natural world. Their diminutive stature and warm fuzzy appearance belies their instinctive ferocity in battle. They may walk upright, but their emotions and instincts are closer to the animals they once were. Confident and unashamed, poporis rarely feel guilt, embarrassment, or sadness.
"Knowledge reveals the past, focuses the present, and kindles the future."

A peaceful and noble race, barakas are nonetheless ferocious in defense of the weak. They are descended from giants, though they have rejected the giants' lust for conquest. Their imposing presence conceals the true strength of their minds; baraka are giants in intellect as well as physicality.
"Faith in others is nothing without faith in one's self."

High elves are eager to prove themselves trustworthy allies of the federation. No one questions their skills, but some question their hearts. The elves strive to overcome their own xenophobia, acquired in the aftermath of an all-too-recent war.
Evasion Tank or Sustained DPS, Melee, Light Armor

Quick attacks and high mobility make warriors essential to group play, but also very survivable while soloing. For tanking, warriors use their Defensive Stance, Cross Parry, and aggro-generating attacks and shouts. In a DPS role, warriors use Assault Stance, which increases Power and Endurance.

Lancers are heavily armored fighters focused on anchoring a battle. They generate maximum threat with shouts and special attacks, sacrificing movement and attack power for the best durability in the game.

Agile fighters who use a devastating greatsword. High damage attacks combine with evasive maneuvers for a dynamic combat style. Slayer skills are quick, precise strikes that knock over and incapacitate even the largest foes, leaving them vulnerable for additional attacks.

Berserkers are constantly in motion, and excel in multiple opponent situations, both as part of a group and solo. They use charge-up attacks to deal massive damage, and can also block incoming frontal attacks. At level 65, this blocking capability is expanded to full tank status.

Sorcerers are spellcasters focused on annihilating enemies with high-damage "nuke" attacks. The mobile artillery of TERA, a sorcerer's job is to kill things quickly. When grouped up, their skills decide which enemy dies first.
Priests are spellcasters whose primary role is to restore health and vitality. However, they are not to be taken lightly—the same power that revives allies can be used to smite foes.
Mystics are a strong healing class with skills to protect and support their party. Mystics also summon powerful thralls to assist and heal them in battle.
Select facial structure and skin tone.

Archers are a highly mobile, ranged combatants. By channeling arcane energy into bows, archers create a wide range of damaging effects. Archer skills can poison, slow, stun, and trap targets, giving them advantages in any encounter.

Gunners are solidly-armored, ranged combatants. Effective from every part of the battlefield, gunners use a variety of potent attacks to pound foes, including some fueled completely by Willpower. Gunner skills focus on dealing damage rather than creating effects, although plenty of the gunner's attacks stagger or knock back enemies!

Brawlers are fast, solidly-armored, hand-to-hand combatants. Built for close-in fighting, brawlers use a variety of powerful blows to pummel enemies, including many fueled completely by Rage. Brawler skills concentrate on dealing damage, but lots of brawler attacks knock enemies around the battlefield!

Ninjas are quick, deadly combatants with the ability to evade enemy attacks. A ninja's agility and mobility more than compensate for the lowered defense of cloth armor—and their damage output places them solidly on the front lines of any fight.

Declaring GvG battle:
* Battle begins 5min after GvG declaration and lasts until withdrawal or surrender.
* Declaration costs guild funds, and the cost depends on the size of the declaring guild. (Small guilds: 300, medium: 900, large: 1,500 guild funds)
* Declaring guilds must pay a declaration penalty every hour until the other guild surrenders or declares mutual GvG. (Small guilds: 5, medium: 15, large: 25 guild funds per hour)

Ending GvG battle:
* Declaring guilds can withdraw their declaration if the other guild does not surrender or declares mutual GvG.
* Defending guild can surrender after 30 minutes, but must compensate the declaring guild with guild funds.

<font size='20'>What is a Guild Conquest Ranked Battle?</font>
You can contest the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle at a set time. The guild with the highest score wins.

<font size='20'>Guild Conquest Ranked Battle: Personal Ranking</font>
During the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle, your character's highest score will be recorded.
Your score will be compared with all other characters in the same class. This is used to calculate your personal ranking.

<font size='20'>Guild Conquest Ranked Battle: Guild Ranking</font>
The guild ranking is the sum of the high scores of all the guild members.

<font size='20'>Guild Conquest Ranked Battle: Reward</font>
At the end of the event, you will receive rewards based on your guild ranking and your personal ranking in your class.

<font size='20'>Guild Conquest Ranked Battle: Entry</font>
The Guild Conquest Ranked Battle can be entered by one player or up to the specified number of players.
You should enter the dungeon with the maximum number of players to achieve the highest possible score.

<font size='20'>Guild Conquest Ranked Battle: Entry Location</font>
You can enter the Ranking Battle via the NPC for the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle in each capital city.

<font size='20'>Implementation and end of the Coop Dungeon</font>
The battle is ended either by a time limit or when all group members are incapacitated. The scores are then calculated.

<font size='20'>Caution: Joining and leaving a guild</font>
If a guild record has already been set, but you leave the guild or join a new one, your record for the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle will be deleted. If you leave a guild without setting a record in the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle, the record will be recalculated when you join a new guild. If you leave a guild that has participated in the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle and rejoin it, the guild's current record will apply for you.

<font size='20'>Guild Conquest Ranked Battle record of a guild deserter</font>
The record of a guild member who leaves the guild during the event remains until the end of the event.

<font size='20'>Calculating the high score at the end of the event</font>
When the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle event ends, the maximum number of guild members that have set a record in the Ranked Battle cannot be exceeded. Finally, only the records of guild members who achieved the highest scores are included in the calculation.

<font size='20'>Reward</font>
If a Guild Conquest Ranked Battle is completed properly, a drop item can be obtained, depending on the dungeon. When the Guild Conquest Ranked Battle event period ends, the reward based on the guild ranking will be sent to all guild members by parcel post. You will also receive a reward based on your personal ranking.

<font size='20'>Changing the guild history of a group member before a Ranked Battle</font>
If a party member's guild is disbanded, a member leaves the guild, or a member is kicked out before a Guild Conquest Ranked Battle, the score of all the group members will not be counted in the rankings.
There is no reward for another guild member's ranking.
